I like having my urgent_workspace displayed as bright red, but I also have fairly modal based keybindings and seeing a bright red box flash is a bit distracting.

Is there a separate color setting when displaying the mode?
</description><pubDate>Mon, 28 Oct 2013 20:27:21 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2793/i3bar-color-setting-for-mode-vs-urgent_workspace/</guid></item><item><title>Answer by Adaephon for &lt;p&gt;When entering a mode, such as the "resize" mode which is provided as a default, the i3bar displays the mode using the urgent_workspace color setting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I like having my urgent_workspace displayed as bright red, but I also have fairly modal based keybindings and seeing a bright red box flash is a bit distracting.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is there a separate color setting when displaying the mode?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2793/i3bar-color-setting-for-mode-vs-urgent_workspace/?answer=2794#post-id-2794</link><description>At the moment there is no separate color setting for displaying the current mode. 

If this keeps bugging you, you may want to [open a new i3 ticket](http://newticket.i3wm.org/) for a feature request.</description><pubDate>Tue, 29 Oct 2013 07:11:01 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/2793/i3bar-color-setting-for-mode-vs-urgent_workspace/?answer=2794#post-id-2794</guid></item></channel></rss>